HEADWORD: Prognosis
<hw>Prog*no"sis</hw> <pr>(pr⟦ocr⟧g*n⟦omac⟧"s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>pro`gnosis</grk>, fr. <grk>progignw`skein</grk>
to know beforehand; <grk>pro`</grk> before + <grk>gignw`skein</grk> to
know. See <er>Know</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The act or art of
foretelling the course and termination of a disease; also, the outlook
afforded by this act of judgment; <as>as, the <ex>prognosis</ex> of
hydrophobia is bad</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prognostic</ent>⟦br⟧
